{"word":"ἀντιβολέω","slug":"ἀντιβολέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀντιβολέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀντιβάλλω'><el>ἀντιβάλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to meet by chance</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> in battle, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> or <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> rei, <i>to be present at</i>, <el>φόνωι ἀνδρῶν, τάφωι ἀνδρῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to partake of, have one's share of</i>, <el>μάχης</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>τάφου</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>to fall to one's lot</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <el>γάμος ἀντιβολήσει ἐμέθεν</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to meet as a suppliant, entreat, supplicate</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to supplicate, entreat</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}